# Reader Persona - [COMPANY NAME]

Note: this is the reader persona for blog content, not the sales ICP. They may overlap, but the reader
might be one level below the buyer (e.g. a technical expert instead of C-level) or broader (the wider
market of potential customers).

## Primary Reader Profile

- **Role:** [e.g. Production Manager, Startup CTO, Head of Operations]
- **Company:** [e.g. Industrial manufacturer, 50-500 employees, North America]
- **Knowledge level:** [Beginner / Intermediate / Expert] in the topics we cover
- **How they find articles:** [Google search / AI search / referral / newsletter / LinkedIn]

## Secondary Readers (Buying Committee)

Who else reads this content besides the primary reader? These people influence or approve buying decisions.

- **[Role, e.g. CFO]** - reads to understand [e.g. "ROI and cost justification"]
- **[Role, e.g. IT Director]** - reads to evaluate [e.g. "integration complexity and security"]
- **[Role, e.g. End User / Operator]** - reads to check [e.g. "daily usability and learning curve"]

How this affects content: [e.g. "Include an ROI section in every commercial-intent article. Keep technical depth but add a summary box for non-technical stakeholders."]

