## Purchase Triggers

What specifically drives them to start looking for a solution?
- [e.g. "A project that missed its deadline"]
- [e.g. "A conversation with a competitor who has better results"]
- [e.g. "Board pressure to cut costs by 15%"]
- [e.g. "A new hire who used a better tool at their previous company"]

## What Convinces Them

[Which arguments, formats, and evidence resonate with this persona?]
- [e.g. "Case studies with numbers from their industry"]
- [e.g. "Step-by-step comparisons with their current process"]
- [e.g. "Testimonials from people in the same role"]
- [e.g. "Clear pricing and implementation timelines"]

## What Repels Them

[What do they avoid? What triggers skepticism?]
- [e.g. "Marketing promises without data to back them up"]
- [e.g. "Overly technical jargon when they're an operations manager, not an engineer"]
- [e.g. "Content that clearly was written by AI without expert review"]

## Content Consumption Habits

Where and how does this reader consume professional content?

- **Primary channels:** [e.g. "LinkedIn feed, Google search during work hours, industry newsletters"]
- **Preferred formats:** [e.g. "Short how-to articles (under 10 min read), comparison tables, video walkthroughs"]
- **Reading context:** [e.g. "At desk during work, on mobile between meetings, forwarded by a colleague"]
- **Communities and forums:** [e.g. "Reddit r/manufacturing, LinkedIn groups for operations leaders, Hacker News"]
- **Trusted publications:** [e.g. "Industry Week, MIT Technology Review, vendor blogs they already follow"]
- **Newsletter behavior:** [e.g. "Subscribes to 2-3, skims subject lines, opens only if topic is immediately relevant"]

